    "title": "The Integration of Trust and Law",
    "thesis": "Proverbs 3 is the integration. Where Proverbs 1 ignited the call and Proverbs 2 postured the soul toward it, Proverbs 3 fuses trust and law into a single architecture. The chapter teaches that identity rests in law not because law constrains identity, but because law is the structural form of identity itself. To trust the Lord with all the heart is to trust the archetype one has chosen. To acknowledge the Lord in all ways is to remember identity at every motion. The chapter resolves the apparent tension between rest and discipline: they are the same motion, viewed from different planes.",
